Paul Weiner


Obituary
Condolences




























Family-Placed Death Notice WEINER, Paul Paul S. Weiner, 88, of Jonesboro, passed away peacefully on Sunday, February 12, 2012. Born in Baltimore, Maryland, he was a WWII and Korean War Army Veteran. Paul went on to graduate from John Marshall Law School in Atlanta in 1968 and practiced law for 43 years. He is survived by his sons, Paul J. Weiner and Jeff Gruber and his wife Sherry; his daughters, Tracy Victoria Weiner and her husband Tim Bowers, IliSi Malone, Leisa Weiner, Sabrina Yokeley and her husband David, Tonya Williams and her husband Tom, and Kristy Schueneman and her husband Trent; 14 grandchildren; and 4 great-grandchildren. An on-line guestbook is available at www.edressler.com and in lieu of flowers, memorial donations may be made to the Kidney Foundation or the . Private services will be held at Georgia National Cemetery in Canton and a celebration of his life will be held from 5-8pm on Wednesday, February 15, 2012 at Pristine Chapel, 7541 Mount Zion Blvd., Jonesboro, GA 30236. Arrangements by Dressler's Jewish Funeral Care, 770-451-4999.
					


Published in The Atlanta Journal-Constitution on Feb. 14, 2012


